    {
      "id": "paper_1:introduction:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "intro_1",
      "text": "There are several underlying causes for adrenal insufficiency, where an autoimmune attack by the immune system is the most common cause.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:clinical:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "clinical_1",
      "text": "Primary AI (PAI), also known as Addison's disease, is a rare disease with a prevalence of approximately 100 per million in Europe",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:diagnosis:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "diagnosis_1",
      "text": "Morning cortisol concentration <140 nmol/L and an ACTH concentration twice the upper reference limit verifies a PAI diagnosis",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:diagnosis:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "diagnosis_2",
      "text": "A healthy person is expected to have >500 nmol/L of plasma cortisol concentration 60 minutes after 250\u00b5g cosyntropin injection",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:autoantibodies:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "autoantibodies_1",
      "text": "21OH-Abs are found in 80\u201390% of patients with PAI in cross-sectional studies after exclusion of known non-autoimmune causes",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:genetics:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "genetics_1",
      "text": "Skov and collaborators recently showed, by analyzing 29 twin pairs with PAI, a concordance for monozygotic twins of 0.71 and a heritability of 0.97, revealing that PAI is a highly genetic disorder",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:treatment:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "treatment_1",
      "text": "The standard medication of glucocorticoid treatment for patients with AI (primary and secondary) is hydrocortisone or cortisone acetate",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "review",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_1:treatment:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_1",
      "text_span_id": "treatment_2",
      "text": "Patients with primary AI additionally take fludrocortisone treatment for mineralocorticoid deficiency",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
